<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="no-churn-cream" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Ice Cream (No Churn)</title>

  <p>
    Ingredients:
  </p>
  <tabular>
    <row>
      <cell>14 ounce can sweetened condensed milk</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>2 teaspoons vanilla extract</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{8}</m> teaspoon salt</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
    <cell>2 cups heavy cream, cold</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>Mix-in options:  Cookies, peanut butter cups, Heath bar, Butterfinger</cell>
    </row>
  </tabular>

  <p>Instructions
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          Whisk together condensed milk, vanilla, and salt in a large bowl.  Set aside.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Whip cream in mixer on medium-high speed until firm peaks form (about 2 minutes).  Fold about 1 cup of the whipped cream into the condensed milk mixture with rubber spatula until combined.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Fold the lightened mixture into the remaining whipped cream until well blended.  Pour into a chilled 9" x 5" x 3" metal loaf pan. 
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Freeze, covered, until thick and creamy (about 2 hours).  Swirl in mix-ins with a spoon.  Continue to freeze, covered, until solid and scoopable, about 3 hours more.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>

  <p>
    Notes:
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </p>
</section>